-- Cornell Upsets No. 2 Michigan in NCAA Ice Hockey Tournament
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-03-24T04:28:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-24/cornell-upsets-no-2-michigan-in-ncaa-ice-hockey-tournament.html
Rodger Craig scored the game-
winning goal in overtime as No. 14-seeded  Cornell University 
upset the second-seeded University of Michigan 3-2 in the
national men’s college ice hockey tournament.  Cornell advanced to the second round against Ferris State
today in the National Collegiate Athletic Association
tournament. Simon Denis scored the deciding goal three minutes
into the third period last night to give Ferris State a 2-1 win
against Denver.  Jeremy Welsh had the go-ahead goal in the second period as
third-seeded Union College defeated No. 15 Michigan State 3-1 to
reach the second round today against No. 13 Massachusetts-
Lowell. Riley Wetmore scored his second goal of the game in
overtime to give Massachusetts-Lowell a 4-3 victory against
seventh-seeded Miami of Ohio.  In today’s other first-round games, it is top-ranked  Boston
College  facing the Air Force Academy, Minnesota-Duluth against
Maine, Minnesota-Twin Cities playing  Boston University (43751MF)  and
Western Michigan meeting No. 4  North Dakota .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
